Thanks for the link, it helped me get there. I followed the documentation and tutorials for nodejs/express which defined the cert and key. As your link suggested, mobile browsers are less lenient about missing intermediate ca information so adding this solved it:<p><pre><code>    var express = require(&#x27;express&#x27;),
        path = require(&#x27;path&#x27;),
        http = require(&#x27;http&#x27;),
        https = require(&#x27;https&#x27;),
        fs = require (&#x27;fs&#x27;);

    var app = express();

    var options = {
      key: fs.readFileSync(&#x27;cert/rsa.key&#x27;),
      cert: fs.readFileSync(&#x27;cert/rsa.crt&#x27;),
      ca: fs.readFileSync(&#x27;cert/sub.class1.server.ca.pem&#x27;) // needed this
    };

    https.createServer(options, app).listen(443);</code></pre>
